Parliament, Thursday, 29 October 2020 – The Standing Committee on Public Accounts (Scopa) will tomorrow conduct an oversight visit to the Unemployment Insurance Fund (UIF). The oversight visit will give the committee a better understanding of the issues relating to the internal control systems, including the disbursement of UIF Covid-19 funds. Scopa will be joined by the Portfolio Committee on Employment and Labour.
	 
	Details of the meeting are as follows: 
	Date: Friday, 30 October 2020
	Time:  08:15
	Venue: 230 Lillian Ngoyi Street, Absa Towers, Pretoria
	 
	Programme ISSUED BY THE PARLIAMENTARY COMMUNICATION SERVICES.
	 
	For media enquiries, please contact the Committee’s Media Officer:
